string.name: STR_CASH_QSHOP_PACK_WE_M_80A_DESC
string.body:
Can be used on packable mythical (or lesser) weapons up to level 80 so that they can be traded afterwards.
The packaged item can only be traded once.
Double-click (right-click) on the scroll, then select the item to package.
[Notes]
1. If you receive a packaged item, it is unpacked automatically.
2. If you wear a packaged item, it will be unpacked automatically and the amount of approved packaging will be used up accordingly.
3. If you have packaged an item and you receive it again, it remains packaged (e.g. when cancelling an auction registration, when the time limit is exceeded during registration, when taking back items from the private shop, when a transaction is cancelled, when processing or returning items in the post, or when posting to yourself).
4. Packaging possible: items that have received additional packaging after enchantment, manastone socketing, DP augmentation, magic augmentation, Idian enhancement, plastic surgery, or from Enchantment Level 20.
5. Packaging not possible: for items that have been armed or already packed, for stacking, Armsfusion, and prior to identification.
6. The following actions are not possible in packaged state: extraction, enchantment, manastone socketing, godstone socketing, Idian enhancement, DP augmentation, magic augmentation, dyeing and plastic surgery, manastone removal, colour or secondary weapon, Armsfusion.

string.name: STR_CASH_QSHOP_MATTER_ENCHANT_STIGMA_DESC
string.body:
Can enchant certain Stigmas.
If the enchantment is successful, the level is increased by 1. There is a slight possibility that the level may also increase by 2 or 3.
If the attempt fails, the level is reduced by 1. There is a slight possibility that the previous level will remain unchanged.
Activate the Stigma Enchantment Stone by double-clicking or right-clicking it, and then select the Stigma you want to enchant.

string.name: STR_CASH_KISK_LIGHT_PARTY_SMALL_HIDE_01_DESC
string.body:
Summons a camouflaged Kisk which resurrects the fallen at its location. It lasts for 2 hours, can be activated by up to 6 people and allows 18 resurrections.
Only usable by members of the same group as the Spiritmaster.
You can change the mode of a disguised Kisk again when you use the "Penetrate" or "Searching Eye" skills.
The player who positions it remains semi-transparent.
Once you position it, the time remaining until you can reuse it is displayed.

string.name: STR_INGAME_MATTER_ENCHANT_STIGMA_DESC
string.body:
Can enchant certain Stigmas.
If the enchantment is successful, the level is increased by 1. There is a slight possibility that the level may also increase by 2 or 3.
If the attempt fails, the level is reduced by 1. There is a slight possibility that the previous level will remain unchanged.
Activate the Stigma Enchantment Stone by double-clicking or right-clicking it, and then select the Stigma you want to enchant.

string.name: STR_EVENT_REWARD_MATTER_ENCHANT_STIGMA_DESC
string.body:
Can enchant certain Stigmas.
If the enchantment is successful, the level is increased by 1. There is a slight possibility that the level may also increase by 2 or 3.
If the attempt fails, the level is reduced by 1. There is a slight possibility that the previous level will remain unchanged.
Activate the Stigma Enchantment Stone by double-clicking or right-clicking it, and then select the Stigma you want to enchant.
This item will disappear at the end of the event.
